      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is very risky to try to self-medicate or alter your prescribed dosage, even with the intention of making it \"safer.\" The interaction between diazepam and alcohol is not linear; what seems like a compromise can still lead to dangerous levels of sedation or impaired function. If you are struggling to sleep, the best and safest course of action is to immediately contact your physician to discuss adjusting your treatment plan. Do not make changes to your medication regimen on your own.",
      "source": "target",
